.TH "vmw_legacy_srf_bind" 9 "vmw_legacy_srf_bind" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_legacy_srf_bind \- Perform a legacy surface bind as part of the surface validation process.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_legacy_srf_bind
.BI "(struct vmw_resource *res "  ","
.BI "struct ttm_validate_buffer *val_buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "res" 12
Pointer to a struct vmw_res embedded in a struct
vmw_surface.
.IP "val_buf" 12
Pointer to a struct ttm_validate_buffer containing
information about the backup buffer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will copy backup data to the surface if the
backup buffer is dirty.
